    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Time Expressions: In the morning, In the evening/at night"
        },
        "text": "To specify when activities happen, you'll need time expressions like 'in the morning' and 'in the evening/at night'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "في الصباح",
            "english": "In the morning",
            "transliteration": "fi as-sabah"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "في المساء",
            "english": "In the evening / At night",
            "transliteration": "fi al-masaa'"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أستيقظ في الصباح.",
            "english": "I wake up in the morning.",
            "transliteration": "astayqithu fi as-sabah."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Verb: I drink (أشرب)"
        },
        "text": "'أشرب' means 'I drink'. This verb, like 'آكل', is essential for talking about your daily intake. It is also in the present tense, first person singular.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أشربُ",
            "english": "I drink",
            "transliteration": "ashrabu"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أشرب القهوة في الصباح.",
            "english": "I drink coffee in the morning.",
            "transliteration": "ashrabu al-qahwah fi as-sabah."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
