        "title": {
          "english": "Verb: I go (أذهب) and the preposition 'to' (إلى)"
        },
        "text": "The verb 'أذهب' means 'I go'. When going 'to' a place, you use the preposition 'إلى'.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "أذهبُ",
            "english": "I go",
            "transliteration": "ath-habu"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "إلى",
            "english": "To",
            "transliteration": "ila"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أذهبُ إلى العمل.",
            "english": "I go to work.",
            "transliteration": "ath-habu ila al-'amal."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Daily Activities: Work and Study"
        },
        "text": "Here are common destinations for daily routines.",
        "examples": [
          {
            "arabic": "العمل",
            "english": "The work / Work",
            "transliteration": "al-'amal"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "الدراسة",
            "english": "The study / Studying",
            "transliteration": "ad-dirasah"
          },
          {
            "arabic": "أذهب إلى الدراسة.",
            "english": "I go to study (e.g., to school/university).",
            "transliteration": "ath-habu ila ad-dirasah."
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "content",
      "content": {
        "title": {
          "english": "Connectors: Then (ثم), After that (بعد ذلك)"
        },
        "text": "To link different activities in your daily program, you can use these connectors.",
        "examples": [
